OL,3,COne in eight households skipping meals
OL,4,Camid cost of food crisis
OL,6,FCertain groups of consumers were more
OL,7,Flikely to have skipped meals - one in
OL,8,Ffive renters and a quarter of those
OL,9,Fwho are unemployed missing meals.
OL,11,FThe majority of households (53%) also
OL,12,Freported buying cheaper products and
OL,13,Falmost half (46%) said they purchased
OL,14,Fmore supermarket own-brand budget
OL,15,Frange items to cut grocery costs.
OL,17,FInflation also remains a problem for
OL,18,Fthe price of fruit, vegetables, and
OL,19,Fdairy in the UK.
