OL,6,FThe Priority Places for Food Index
OL,7,Fdeveloped jointly by Which? and the
OL,8,FConsumer Data Research Centre at the
OL,9,FUniversity of Leeds, has also been
OL,10,Fupdated to reveal the local areas in
OL,11,Fthe UK where households are most
OL,12,Flikely to be in need of extra support
OL,13,Fto put food on the table.
OL,15,FIn England, the North East, Yorkshire
OL,16,Fand the Humber and the West Midlands
OL,17,Fhad the highest number of priority
OL,18,Fplace areas.
